social_posts.post_text: It’s my EARTH DAY! I am sooooo happy to spend it here in Ghana with family and friends… the past year has been an interesting one, ups & downs, weird people, hospital visits… But finally now closure, understanding, more light and great health. I am mad grateful for this vessel of mine and all the patience she has for me, I am so crazy grateful for all the experiences I have whether good or bad and I’m just so humble to be here with so much love around me. L I G H T ✨🤍✨

V O I C E S O U N D N O I S E  In the constant dance between thoughts and confusion, we try to find a steady rhythm. Think of poetry like wind - a beacon that sways back and forth, vibrating with the language of the cosmos. This journey, expressed in poetry, dances to the rhythm of 'chaosmosis', the joint evolution of our thoughts and the world around us. In this way, poetry (like the wind) weaves chaos into harmony, showing the easy flow between a universe made of words and movement.  artist - @lalanana7
